<OUTPUT_TEXT>
To prepare for trial by organizing exhibits:

1. Create an exhibit list
2. Assign unique numbers/letters to each exhibit
3. Make copies of all exhibits (physical and digital)
4. Organize exhibits in clearly labeled folders or binders
5. Prepare exhibit stickers or labels
6. Create an electronic database of exhibits
7. Ensure all exhibits are admissible and relevant
8. Coordinate with attorneys on exhibit presentation order
9. Prepare exhibit boards or digital presentations if needed
10. Double-check for completeness and accuracy
11. Have backup copies of all exhibits readily available
</OUTPUT_TEXT>
